ffers a selection of the most important source material allowing readers to enter these debates themselves.Key features:central issues in modern debates about Roman imperialism are identified and discussedkey texts in translation along with key images are gathered and made accessibleincludes a comprehensive timeline, glossary, further reading and useful website resources Andrew Erskine is Professor of Ancient History at the University of Edinburgh.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aImperialism. 4aClassics & Ancient History. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / Rome.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z97831107804680 cprintz978074861962740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074862905340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748629053423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748629053/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK